      \"Politely excuse yourself and leave the room to avoid being associated with the conversation.\",
      \"Privately speak to the senior doctor later to express your discomfort and remind them of professional conduct.\",
      \"Report the doctor's behaviour immediately to the head of department.\"
    ],
    \"correct_answer\": 2,
    \"explanation\": \"Addressing the issue privately and respectfully with the doctor is often the most appropriate first step. It allows the doctor to reflect on their conduct without immediate formal escalation, which might be disproportionate for a first instance. Leaving the room avoids the situation but doesn't address the unprofessional behaviour. Joining in, even with good intentions, could be misconstrued. Immediately reporting could be seen as an overreaction, especially if a direct conversation could resolve the issue.\",
    \"metadata\": {
      \"difficulty\": \"medium\",
      \"section_type\": \"situational_judgement\"
    }
  },
  {
    \"type\": \"situational_judgement\",
    \"topic\": \"Teamwork & Communication\",
    \"stem\": \"You are part of a team presenting a complex case study. A team member, Sarah, has consistently failed to complete her assigned sections, leaving you and others to pick up her slack just before the deadline. This has happened multiple times.\",
