    \"correct_answer\": 1,
    \"explanation\": \"Poor hand hygiene poses a significant risk to patient safety. The most appropriate first step is to address the issue privately and respectfully with your colleague. This allows them to correct their behaviour without unnecessary formal escalation. If the behaviour persists after this, then escalation to a ward manager or infection control lead would be appropriate. Publicly shaming is unprofessional.\",
    \"metadata\": {
      \"difficulty\": \"medium\",
      \"section_type\": \"situational_judgement\"
