    \"correct_answer\": 2,
    \"explanation\": \"The duty of candour requires openness and honesty with patients when something goes wrong. It's crucial that the patient and family are fully informed. Your role is to ensure this happens by discussing your concerns with the consultant. You should not inform the patient yourself before speaking to the consultant, as this could cause confusion or undermine the team. Documenting without discussion is insufficient.\",
