    \"correct_answer\": 1,
    \"explanation\": \"Maintaining professional boundaries and adhering to hospital policy regarding gifts is crucial. Accepting expensive gifts can create perceived obligations or conflicts of interest. Politely declining and explaining the policy is the most professional response. Accepting and donating or keeping it secretly still violates the spirit of the policy.\",
    \"metadata\": {
      \"difficulty\": \"medium\",
      \"section_type\": \"situational_judgement\"
