    \"correct_answer\": 2,
    \"explanation\": \"Patient-centred care involves respecting patient preferences while providing evidence-based information. Engaging in a shared decision-making process, where you explain options and understand their perspective, is the most ethical and effective approach. Insisting or dismissing their preference undermines autonomy. Referring them without attempting to find common ground is not ideal.\",
