    \"correct_answer\": 2,
    \"explanation\": \"It's important to manage patient expectations empathetically and realistically. Listen to their concerns, acknowledge their hopes, and then provide clear, evidence-based information. Focusing on symptom management and quality of life is key for chronic conditions. Bluntly dismissing their beliefs can damage rapport. Agreeing to unproven therapies is unethical. Referring them without managing expectations is irresponsible.\",
    \"metadata\": {
      \"difficulty\": \"medium\",
      \"section_type\": \"situational_judgement\"
    }
  },
  {
    \"type\": \"situational_judgement\",
