    \"explanation\": \"In understaffed situations, prioritisation, communication, and seeking help are crucial. You must focus on patient safety first, and then inform your senior about the situation so they can make informed decisions about resource allocation or additional support. Delegating beyond scope of practice is unsafe. Trying to do everything yourself can lead to burnout and errors.\",
    \"metadata\": {
      \"difficulty\": \"medium\",
      \"section_type\": \"situational_judgement\"
