    \"correct_answer\": 2,
    \"explanation\": \"Unencrypted patient data on a lost USB stick is a serious data breach risk. You must immediately secure the device and report it to the appropriate authority (IT or your supervisor) so they can follow data breach protocols. Plugging it in yourself could compromise the data further. Leaving it or handing it to a random colleague is irresponsible.\",
