    \"explanation\": \"Ensuring a patient understands their discharge instructions is critical for their safety and recovery. It's your responsibility to confirm understanding, even if it takes extra time. Using 'teach-back' (asking the patient to explain in their own words) is an effective method. Assuming they will figure it out or just repeating verbatim is insufficient. Relying solely on family is not ideal.\",
