  {
    \"type\": \"situational_judgement\",
    \"topic\": \"Ethical Dilemma - Disclosure\",
    \"stem\": \"A patient asks you directly if they are going to die, after receiving a very serious diagnosis. You know their prognosis is poor, but the consultant has not yet had the full conversation with them.\",
    \"passage\": null,
    \"options\": [
      \"Tell them truthfully that their prognosis is very poor, as they have a right to know.\",
      \"Lie and tell them they will be fine, to maintain hope.\",
