    \"explanation\": \"Academic integrity is paramount. While it's difficult to report a friend, allowing cheating undermines the fairness of the assessment and the integrity of the profession. Discreetly reporting to the invigilator is the correct action. Confronting during the exam is disruptive. Telling them to stop but not reporting means the incident is not formally addressed.\",
    \"metadata\": {
      \"difficulty\": \"medium\",
      \"section_type\": \"situational_judgement\"
    }
  },
  {
