  {
    \"type\": \"situational_judgement\",
    \"topic\": \"Professionalism & Integrity\",
    \"stem\": \"You are asked to provide a reference for a student you vaguely remember from a group project, but you don't feel you know enough about their individual performance to write a meaningful reference.\",
    \"passage\": null,
    \"options\": [
      \"Write a generic, positive reference to be helpful.\",
      \"Decline to provide a reference, explaining that you don't have sufficient knowledge of their individual performance.\",
      \"Ask other team members to contribute points for the reference.\",
      \"Agree to write it and then try to remember positive things about them.\"
    ],
    \"correct_answer\": 1,
    \"explanation\": \"Professional integrity requires you to provide references based on genuine knowledge. If you cannot write a meaningful reference about individual performance, it's best to politely decline. This allows the student to seek a referee who can provide a stronger, more informed endorsement. Writing a generic reference is unhelpful.\",
    \"metadata\": {
      \"difficulty\": \"medium\",
      \"section_type\": \"situational_judgement\"
    }
  },
  {
    \"type\": \"situational_judgement\",
    \"topic\": \"Dealing with Ethical Dilemmas\",
    \"stem\": \"A terminally ill patient, in severe pain and with full capacity, expresses a wish to end their life and asks for your assistance in doing so.\",
    \"passage\": null,
    \"options\": [
      \"Tell them you cannot help them, but offer to provide information on euthanasia options in other countries.\",
      \"Express empathy for their suffering, explain that assisting with suicide is illegal and unethical, but reassure them you will do everything possible to manage their pain and symptoms, and offer psychological and palliative care support.\",
      \"Report their request to the police immediately.\",
      \"Ignore their request and change the subject.\"
    ],
    \"correct_answer\": 1,
    \"explanation\": \"Assisting with suicide is illegal and unethical in most jurisdictions. You must not participate. However, you must respond with compassion, address their suffering, and ensure they receive optimal palliative care, pain management, and psychological support. Reporting to police might be necessary if you believe there is immediate intent and means, but empathy and support are paramount first. Ignoring their request is dismissive.\",
    \"metadata\": {
      \"difficulty\": \"medium\",
      \"section_type\": \"situational_judgement\"
    }
  },
  {
    \"type\": \"situational_judgement\",
    \"topic\": \"Professionalism & Boundaries\",
    \"stem\": \"You receive a message on a professional networking site (e.g., LinkedIn) from a patient you previously treated, expressing gratitude and asking to connect professionally.\",
    \"passage\": null,
    \"options\": [
      \"Accept the request, as it's a professional platform.\",
      \"Politely decline, explaining that maintaining clear professional boundaries is important, even on professional networking sites, to avoid blurring the doctor-patient relationship.\",
      \"Accept the request but ensure your profile is very private.\",
      \"Report the patient for inappropriate contact.\"
    ],
    \"correct_answer\": 1,
    \"explanation\": \"While LinkedIn is a professional platform, connecting with current or former patients can still blur professional boundaries. It's generally advisable to maintain a clear distinction to preserve the therapeutic relationship and objectivity. A polite decline with a professional explanation is the best approach.\",
    \"metadata\": {
      \"difficulty\": \"medium\",
      \"section_type\": \"situational_judgement\"
    }
  },
  {
    \"type\": \"situational_judgement\",
    \"topic\": \"Patient Safety & Handover\",
    \"stem\": \"You are conducting a handover. A colleague tries to interrupt you repeatedly with non-urgent questions about another patient, making it difficult to deliver the critical information.\",
    \"passage\": null,
    \"options\": [
      \"Stop your handover and answer their questions to be helpful.\",
      \"Raise your voice to ensure you can be heard over them.\",
      \"Politely but firmly state that you need to complete the critical handover first for patient safety, and you will address their questions afterwards.\",
      \"Ignore them and continue your handover, hoping they get the hint.\"
    ],
    \"correct_answer\": 2,
    \"explanation\": \"Critical handover information must be delivered clearly and without interruption for patient safety. You must politely but firmly assert the importance of completing the handover first, then offer to address their questions. Stopping or raising your voice is unprofessional. Ignoring might not be effective.\",
    \"metadata\": {
      \"difficulty\": \"medium\",
      \"section_type\": \"situational_judgement\"
    }
  },
  {
    \"type\": \"situational_judgement\",
    \"topic\": \"Professional Development & Self-Care\",
    \"stem\": \"You have a demanding study schedule and are starting to feel burnt out, constantly tired and losing motivation. You still have many commitments.\",
    \"passage\": null,
    \"options\": [
      \"Push through the burnout, as there's no time to rest.\",
      \"Take an extended break from all studies and commitments immediately.\",
      \"Review your schedule, identify areas where you can incorporate short breaks and self-care activities, and seek advice from a mentor or student support services on managing workload and stress.\",
      \"Complain to your friends about how difficult medicine is.\"
    ],
    \"correct_answer\": 2,
    \"explanation\": \"Recognising and addressing burnout is crucial for long-term sustainability in medicine. A proactive approach involves reviewing your schedule, prioritising self-care, and seeking support. Pushing through can worsen burnout. Taking an extended break might not be feasible. Complaining is unhelpful.\",
    \"metadata\": {
      \"difficulty\": \"medium\",
      \"section_type\": \"situational_judgement\"
    }
  },
  {
    \"type\": \"situational_judgement\",
    \"topic\": \"Confidentiality & Public Disclosure\",
    \"stem\": \"You are at a public event and recognise a former patient. They approach you and start discussing their medical condition loudly with you in front of other people.\",
    \"passage\": null,
    \"options\": [
      \"Engage in the discussion, as they initiated it.\",
      \"Politely interrupt, explain that you cannot discuss their medical information in a public setting due to confidentiality, and suggest a private way to communicate if necessary.\",
      \"Quickly walk away to avoid the conversation.\",
      \"Tell them to keep their voice down.\"
    ],
    \"correct_answer\": 1,
    \"explanation\": \"Even if a patient initiates a public discussion, you must uphold confidentiality. You cannot participate in a public discussion about their medical details. Politely explaining this and offering a private alternative is the correct and professional response. Walking away or telling them to be quiet can be perceived as rude.\",
    \"metadata\": {
      \"difficulty\": \"medium\",
      \"section_type\": \"situational_judgement\"
    }
  },
  {
    \"type\": \"situational_judgement\",
    \"topic\": \"Dealing with Ethical Dilemmas\",
    \"stem\": \"A patient asks you to lie to their family about their diagnosis, as they are not ready for them to know the full truth.\",
    \"passage\": null,
    \"options\": [
      \"Agree to lie to the family to respect the patient's wishes.\",
      \"Refuse to lie, and tell the patient that you will inform the family.\",
      \"Explain to the patient that you cannot lie, but you can support them in communicating the information to their family in their own time, and respect their wishes regarding what information is shared by you.\",
      \"Tell the patient you will consider it, but then tell the family the truth.\"
    ],
    \"correct_answer\": 2,
    \"explanation\": \"You cannot lie to a patient's family, as it compromises your integrity and trust. However, you must respect the patient's autonomy regarding who receives their information and when, within ethical and legal limits. The best approach is to explain you cannot lie, but you can support them in controlling the disclosure and will only share information with consent. You must not actively mislead.\",
    \"metadata\": {
      \"difficulty\": \"medium\",
      \"section_type\": \"situational_judgement\"
    }
  },
  {
    \"type\": \"situational_judgement\",
    \"topic\": \"Professionalism & Integrity\",
    \"stem\": \"You are asked to observe a procedure that you have already seen many times. You find yourself feeling bored and distracted during the observation.\",
    \"passage\": null,
    \"options\": [
      \"Excuse yourself from the observation, stating you've seen it before.\",
      \"Pull out your phone to check messages discreetly.\",
      \"Remain engaged and use the opportunity to refine your understanding, observe nuances, or consider teaching points for future learning.\",
      \"Pretend to be engaged but mentally switch off.\"
    ],
    \"correct_answer\": 2,
    \"explanation\": \"Every clinical encounter is a learning opportunity, even for familiar procedures. Maintaining engagement and seeking deeper understanding or identifying teaching points demonstrates professionalism and a commitment to continuous learning. Being distracted or excusing yourself is unprofessional.\",
    \"metadata\": {
      \"difficulty\": \"medium\",
      \"section_type\": \"situational_judgement\"
    }
  },
  {
    \"type\": \"situational_judgement\",
    \"topic\": \"Teamwork & Support\",
    \"stem\": \"A new colleague is struggling to adapt to the fast pace of the emergency department and seems overwhelmed. You notice they are making minor errors and falling behind.\",
    \"passage\": null,
    \"options\": [
      \"Let them figure it out themselves, as everyone has to learn.\",
      \"Publicly point out their mistakes to help them learn faster.\",
      \"Privately offer to help them with tasks, provide guidance, and suggest strategies for time management and prioritisation, while also gently encouraging them to seek support from a senior.\",
      \"Report their struggles to the department head, stating they are not coping.\"
    ],
    \"correct_answer\": 2,
    \"explanation\": \"Supporting new colleagues is vital for team effectiveness and patient safety. Offering private, constructive support, practical help, and guidance, while also suggesting they speak to a senior, is the most appropriate approach. Publicly shaming or immediately reporting is unhelpful and unprofessional.\",
    \"metadata\": {
      \"difficulty\": \"medium\",
      \"section_type\": \"situational_judgement\"
    }
  },
  {
    \"type\": \"situational_judgement\",
    \"topic\": \"Patient Safety & Competence\",
    \"stem\": \"You are a medical student. A patient asks you to perform a simple task (e.g., fetch a glass of water, adjust their bed) that is typically done by nursing staff, because the nurse is busy.\",
    \"passage\": null,
    \"options\": [
      \"Tell the patient you are a medical student and cannot do that, and they should wait for the nurse.\",
      \"Politely inform the nurse about the patient's request, and if appropriate and within your scope, assist the patient yourself.\",
      \"Ignore the patient's request, as it's not your job.\",
      \"Perform the task without checking with the nurse, as it's simple.\"
    ],
    \"correct_answer\": 1,
    \"explanation\": \"While your primary role is learning, patient comfort and basic care are everyone's responsibility. It's appropriate to assist with simple tasks if within your capability and after informing the relevant staff member (the nurse). Directly refusing or ignoring is uncompassionate. Performing without informing the nurse might disrupt their care plan.\",
    \"metadata\": {
      \"difficulty\": \"medium\",
      \"section_type\": \"situational_judgement\"
    }
  },
  {
    \"type\": \"situational_judgement\",
    \"topic\": \"Professionalism & Integrity\",
    \"stem\": \"You are asked to participate in a hospital committee meeting. You have a strong personal opinion on a topic being discussed that could be perceived as biased.\",
    \"passage\": null,
    \"options\": [
      \"Express your strong personal opinion forcefully to sway the committee.\",
      \"Keep quiet and don't contribute to the discussion.\",
      \"Participate in the discussion, but declare your potential bias upfront and ensure your contributions are based on evidence and professional judgment, not just personal opinion.\",
      \"Skip the meeting to avoid expressing your opinion.\"
    ],
    \"correct_answer\": 2,
    \"explanation\": \"Professional integrity requires transparency and objectivity. If you have a potential bias, you should declare it. Then, your contributions should be based on evidence and professional judgment, not solely personal opinion. Avoiding the meeting or being forcefully biased is unprofessional.\",
    \"metadata\": {
      \"difficulty\": \"medium\",
      \"section_type\": \"situational_judgement\"
    }
  },
  {
    \"type\": \"situational_judgement\",
    \"topic\": \"Patient Dignity & Respect\",
    \"stem\": \"You enter a patient's room and find them exposed and struggling to adjust their covers, but the nurse who was just with them has left the room.\",
    \"passage\": null,
    \"options\": [
      \"Leave the room and find the nurse to ask them to return.\",
      \"Immediately help the patient adjust their covers, ensuring their dignity and privacy, and then inform the nurse if appropriate.\",
      \"Call for another nurse to assist.\",
      \"Tell the patient to wait for the nurse.\"
    ],
    \"correct_answer\": 1,
    \"explanation\": \"Patient dignity and privacy are paramount. You should immediately provide assistance to maintain their dignity, regardless of your role, then follow up with the nurse if necessary. Leaving or calling for someone else delays essential immediate care.\",
    \"metadata\": {
      \"difficulty\": \"medium\",
      \"section_type\": \"situational_judgement\"
    }
  },
  {
    \"type\": \"situational_judgement\",
    \"topic\": \"Ethical Dilemma - Best Interest\",
    \"stem\": \"An elderly patient with advanced dementia, who lacks capacity, requires a feeding tube to prevent severe malnutrition. Their adult child, who holds power of attorney for health, is refusing consent, stating the patient 'wouldn't want to live like this'.\",
    \"passage\": null,
    \"options\": [
      \"Respect the child's decision immediately, as they hold power of attorney.\",
      \"Insist on inserting the feeding tube, as it's medically necessary to prevent harm.\",
      \"Engage in a detailed discussion with the child, exploring the patient's past wishes, values, and the medical benefits/burdens of the feeding tube, potentially involving an ethics committee or second medical opinion if disagreement persists, aiming for a decision in the patient's best interest.\",
      \"Seek a court order to insert the feeding tube against the child's wishes.\"
    ],
    \"correct_answer\": 2,
    \"explanation\": \"When a patient lacks capacity, decisions should be made in their best interest, considering their known wishes, values, and the medical assessment. While power of attorney is important, it must align with best interest. A thorough discussion, involving ethics committees if needed, is crucial to navigate this complex situation. Insisting or immediately seeking a court order bypasses this vital discussion.\",
    \"metadata\": {
      \"difficulty\": \"medium\",
      \"section_type\": \"situational_judgement\"
    }
  },
  {
    \"type\": \"situational_judgement\",
    \"topic\": \"Teamwork & Communication\",
    \"stem\": \"During a busy clinic, you notice that a colleague is repeatedly making sarcastic comments to patients who ask 'too many' questions, making the patients visibly uncomfortable.\",
    \"passage\": null,
    \"options\": [
      \"Ignore it, as it's not your place to correct a colleague's communication style.\",
      \"Publicly challenge your colleague to stop making such comments.\",
      \"Privately speak to your colleague, explaining the impact of their comments on patients and the importance of empathetic communication, and suggest alternative approaches.\",
      \"Report your colleague to the clinic manager immediately for unprofessional conduct.\"
    ],
    \"correct_answer\": 2,
    \"explanation\": \"Empathetic communication is crucial in patient care. Sarcasm is unprofessional and can harm patients. The most appropriate first step is a private, constructive conversation with your colleague. This allows them to reflect and change their behaviour. Public challenge is unprofessional. Reporting immediately might be an overreaction for a first instance, but is necessary if the behaviour persists.\",
    \"metadata\": {
      \"difficulty\": \"medium\",
      \"section_type\": \"situational_judgement\"
    }
  },
  {
    \"type\": \"situational_judgement\",
    \"topic\": \"Professionalism & Integrity\",
    \"stem\": \"You are completing a mandatory assessment. You realise you made a small error in one of your answers after submitting it, but before the results are released.\",
    \"passage\": null,
    \"options\": [
      \"Do nothing, as it's already submitted and might not be noticed.\",
      \"Contact the assessor or relevant authority immediately to report the error and ask if there's a procedure for correction.\",
      \"Complain to a friend about the unfairness of the assessment.\",
      \"Try to hack into the system to correct your answer.\"
    ],
    \"correct_answer\": 1,
    \"explanation\": \"Professional integrity requires honesty. If you identify an error, even after submission, you should report it to the relevant authority. This demonstrates integrity and a commitment to accuracy. Doing nothing or attempting to illegally modify your submission is unethical. Complaining is unhelpful.\",
    \"metadata\": {
      \"difficulty\": \"medium\",
      \"section_type\": \"situational_judgement\"
    }
  },
  {
    \"type\": \"situational_judgement\",
    \"topic\": \"Working with Limited Resources\",
    \"stem\": \"Your department is experiencing a shortage of essential medical supplies. You are asked to use a less effective alternative for a patient, but you believe the standard supply is crucial for their optimal care.\",
    \"passage\": null,
    \"options\": [
      \"Comply with the request to use the alternative, as there is a shortage.\",
      \"Use the alternative, but complain to colleagues about the poor resource management.\",
      \"Express your concern to your supervisor, explaining the potential impact on patient care, and explore all possible options for obtaining the standard supply or mitigating the risks of the alternative.\",
      \"Refuse to treat the patient until the standard supply is available.\"
    ],
    \"correct_answer\": 2,
    \"explanation\": \"In situations of resource shortage, patient advocacy is key. You should express your concerns to your supervisor, highlighting the potential impact on patient care, and work collaboratively to find the best possible solution, which might involve exploring alternatives or advocating for the necessary supplies. Refusing treatment is unethical. Complaining without action is unhelpful.\",
    \"metadata\": {
      \"difficulty\": \"medium\",
      \"section_type\": \"situational_judgement\"
    }
  }
